args: There you are; all clean.\nIt is a great boon to have\nsuch fine horses.
Now I just need to give them all\na good brushing and I can... Hmm?
You have horses. Can I ride one?
Certainly. Shall I teach you how?
I see. Did you grow up riding horses?
I had two people who taught me to ride.\nOne was my older brother.
I haven't seen him in a while.\nI wonder where he is...

...This happened a little while ago.
She seemed quite lonely as she spoke
of her brother—he must have been a
very lovely person.
Huh. I always thought she seemed like a\nlittle sister, but I didn't know she really\nWAS someone's little sister.
It's no surprise she'd be lonely if she\nhasn't seen her sibling in a while.\nI know exactly how that feels.
Think we can do something\nto take her mind off it?
I mean, we're both older brothers, yeah?\nAnd while we can't be her family, we can\nat least try and help her have fun.
I suppose we DID just promise\nto all be friends...
Great! Then let's invite her somewhere.
Why did you bring me outside?
'Cause I wanted to show you all the rare\nanimals that live deep inside the forest!
There are loads of cute critters here.\n...Hey, look! There's some now!
Whaaat?! Oh man, that's weird.\nSarisse would have been freakin' out\nif I showed her a bunch of cute animals.
And now it's your turn?\nWhat are you trying to do?
You always have a book with you,\nso I thought I'd read you one of my\nfavorite stories.
Reading is okay, I guess.\nBut I mostly read magical grimoires.
Good enough! See, writing stories is\nsort of a hobby of mine, so I thought\nI'd share my latest work with you.
It's called ＂The Prince of a Lost Country\nand the Swindled—＂
R-really? Gee, Zethia always loved it\nwhen I read to her...
Okay, I don't get how to do this at ALL!\nIt's like little sisters have become a\ntotal mystery to me!
What's going on, you two?\nYou both look terribly depressed.
Well, Veronica was feelin' low after\nbeing separated from her brother,\nso we were tryin' to cheer her up.
But nothing we do makes her happy at all.\nMaybe we're both failures as brothers.
Is that what you've been doing?\nYou can stop doing it now.
You'll never take my brother's place.
Wait, Alfonse! You're ALSO an older \nbrother, right? Because in that case,\nit's time for a Triple Brother Offensive!
It's true that my sister is younger than I,\nbut... Er...
Well, perhaps we could go to town\nand shop for dresses or sweets.
Listen to me. I miss my brother.\nIt makes me sad and lonely.
But I don't want any of you\nto try and take his place.
But if you're sad, what can it hurt?
Because while I'm here, I'm just Veronica.
Not a princess or a sister—just Veronica.\nThat's what you said.
Of course I did. So was it a lie?
What? No! Of course not! Ha ha ha!\nStill, I guess you see us as friends\nmore than we thought, huh?
Heh. I believe they're just glad you\nremembered your promise.
Don't worry. So long as I'm in this castle,\nI'll keep my promises.
Well, we might not be able to become\nyour brothers, but we can still have fun!
